== Lemony Ricotta Crostini ==

Adjust rack to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces; place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Drain and return potatoes to pot.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Thinly slice @chives{1/4%ounce}.

Slice @demi baguette{1} crosswise into 8 rounds (16 rounds for 4 servings); spread out on a #baking sheet{} and drizzle with @olive oil{}. Toast on top rack until golden brown, ~{5-10%minutes}.

Place @ricotta cheese{4%ounce} in a #small bowl{}; add half the lemon zest, 1 TBSP lemon juice, @salt{}, and @pepper{} and stir to combine. Spread ricotta onto toasted baguette rounds; drizzle with @red pepper jam{1}. Sprinkle with half the @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and half the chives.

Serve with your favorite beverage for snacking while you prepare the rest of the meal.

> If preferred to serve the crostini with the main course, toast now and assemble right before serving!

== Prosciutto-Wrapped Apricot Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper.

Lay two slices of @prosciutto{2%ounce} beside each other on a flat surface. Place a chicken cutlet along bottom of slices; tightly roll up prosciutto around chicken. Repeat with remaining prosciutto and chicken.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add wrapped chicken and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a second baking sheet. Wipe out pan.

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through, ~{15%minutes}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Chive Mashed Potatoes ==

Mash potatoes with a #potato masher{} or fork until smooth. Stir in half the @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, remaining chives, and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season generously with salt and pepper. Keep covered until ready to serve.

> If potatoes have cooled, mash over medium-low heat.

== Honey-Apricot Glaze ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for the chicken over low heat. Whisk in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @apricot jam{1}, and half the @honey{2%teaspoon}.

When chicken is done, return to pan with any drippings and turn to coat in sauce.

== Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together half the @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, remaining honey, @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, juice from one lemon wedge, salt, and pepper. Add @mixed greens{2%ounce} to bowl and toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

Slice chicken crosswise. Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and salad between plates. Drizzle chicken with any remaining pan sauce and top salad with remaining almonds.

Serve @cinnamon crumb cake muffin{2} for dessert.